{"title_page": "Between the Bars", "text_new": "{{short description|1997 song by Elliott Smith}}\n{{for|the American blog|Between the Bars (blog)}}\n{{notability|Music|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Between the Bars\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     =\n| artist   = [[Elliott Smith]]\n| album    = [[Either/Or (album)|Either/Or]]\n| released = February 25, 1997\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = [[Indie folk]], [[lo-fi music|lo-fi]], [[sadcore]]\n| length   = 2:21\n| label    = [[Kill Rock Stars]]\n| writer   = Smith\n| producer = Smith, [[Tom Rothrock]], [[Rob Schnapf]]\n}}\n\n\"'''Between the Bars'''\" is the fourth track of [[Elliott Smith]]'s 1997 album ''[[Either/Or (album)|Either/Or]]''. It is written as a short [[ballad]] in the key of G Minor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://findsongtempo.com/artists/elliott-smith/songs/between-the-bars-0444f671-dc32-454b-ac3b-a1c388e2e2ed|title=Between The Bars by Elliott Smith \u2013 Find Song Tempo|website=findsongtempo.com|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> The song is one of three tracks from ''Either/Or'' that was used in the soundtrack of ''[[Good Will Hunting]]''. It is also featured in the 2012 indie film, ''[[Stuck in Love]]'', and in the seventh episode of season two of \"[[Rick and Morty]]\". As of March 2019, the song is his most streamed track {{Citation needed|reason=out pf the blue statement|date=March 2019}} on the popular music streaming services [[Spotify]] and [[Apple Music]]. A cover version of the song performed by Chris Garneau was used in Pedro Almodovar's film \"La piel que habito\" (The skin I live in) in 2012.\n\n== Live performances ==\nSmith performed the song very often, and it was the 13th song of his final performance at Redfest in [[Salt Lake City, Utah]] on September 19, 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setlist.fm/setlist/elliott-smith/2003/redfest-salt-lake-city-ut-6bdf8a16.html|title=Elliott Smith Setlist at Redfest, Salt Lake City|website=setlist.fm|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Cover versions==\n\"Between the Bars\" has been covered by artists such as [[Chris Garneau]], [[Madeleine Peyroux]], [[Glen Phillips (singer)|Glen Phillips]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Kevin Devine]], [[Poppy (entertainer)|Poppy]], [[The Civil Wars]], [[Agnes Obel]], and [[Seth Avett]]/[[Jessica Lea Mayfield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setlist.fm/stats/songs/elliott-smith-1bd6d174.html?song=Between+the+Bars|title=Between the Bars by Elliott Smith Song Statistics \u2013 setlist.fm|website=www.setlist.fm|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n[[Category:Elliott Smith songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about alcohol]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Elliott Smith]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1997 song by Elliott Smith}}\n{{for|the American blog|Between the Bars (blog)}}\n{{notability|Music|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Between the Bars\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     =\n| artist   = [[Elliott Smith]]\n| album    = [[Either/Or (album)|Either/Or]]\n| released = February 25, 1997\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = [[Indie folk]], [[lo-fi music|lo-fi]], [[sadcore]]\n| length   = 2:21\n| label    = [[Kill Rock Stars]]\n| writer   = Smith\n| producer = Smith, [[Tom Rothrock]], [[Rob Schnapf]]\n}}\n\n\"'''Between the Bars'''\" is the fourth track of [[Elliott Smith]]'s 1997 album ''[[Either/Or (album)|Either/Or]]''. It is written as a short ballad in the key of G Minor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://findsongtempo.com/artists/elliott-smith/songs/between-the-bars-0444f671-dc32-454b-ac3b-a1c388e2e2ed|title=Between The Bars by Elliott Smith \u2013 Find Song Tempo|website=findsongtempo.com|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref> The song is one of three tracks from ''Either/Or'' that was used in the soundtrack of ''[[Good Will Hunting]]''. It is also featured in the 2012 indie film, ''[[Stuck in Love]]'', and in the seventh episode of season two of \"[[Rick and Morty]]\". As of March 2019, the song is his most streamed track {{Citation needed|reason=out pf the blue statement|date=March 2019}} on the popular music streaming services [[Spotify]] and [[Apple Music]]. A cover version of the song performed by Chris Garneau was used in Pedro Almodovar's film \"La piel que habito\" (The skin I live in) in 2012.\n\n== Live performances ==\nSmith performed the song very often, and it was the 13th song of his final performance at Redfest in [[Salt Lake City, Utah]] on September 19, 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setlist.fm/setlist/elliott-smith/2003/redfest-salt-lake-city-ut-6bdf8a16.html|title=Elliott Smith Setlist at Redfest, Salt Lake City|website=setlist.fm|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Cover versions==\n\"Between the Bars\" has been covered by artists such as [[Chris Garneau]], [[Madeleine Peyroux]], [[Glen Phillips (singer)|Glen Phillips]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Kevin Devine]], [[Poppy (entertainer)|Poppy]], [[The Civil Wars]], [[Agnes Obel]], and [[Seth Avett]]/[[Jessica Lea Mayfield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setlist.fm/stats/songs/elliott-smith-1bd6d174.html?song=Between+the+Bars|title=Between the Bars by Elliott Smith Song Statistics \u2013 setlist.fm|website=www.setlist.fm|accessdate=June 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n[[Category:Elliott Smith songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about alcohol]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Elliott Smith]]\n", "name_user": "Pyrodney", "label": "safe", "comment": "Hyperlinked 'ballad'", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Between_the_Bars"}
